lving novel Tb1 and AlphaCoVs identified in Eptesicus fuscus (family Vespertilionidae) from the U.S. The putative recombinant region is in the S1 subdomain of the Spike gene, encompass\u00ad ing the potential receptor-binding domain of AlphaCoVs. This study reports the first AlphaCoV genomes in molossids from the Americas and provides new insights into recombination as an important mode of evolution of coronaviruses involved in crossspecies transmission.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Cerri, Agustina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bolatti, Elisa M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zorec, Tomaz M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Montani, Maria E.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rimondi, Agustina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hosnjak, Lea", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Casal, Pablo E.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Di Domenica, Violeta", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Barquez, Ruben M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Poljak, Mario", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Giri, Adriana A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "He, Biao", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/0b5083c6441cb61bf5038b1d1b179ba4", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/9df5bde8e1c9629f88a69cfa1a32195f4cb23e57cd783f3047816b65f040e20b", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/XSR5T3LR", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/XSR5T3LR", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/3539add6bb1e7964cf68be60958dc8f6!/b49942-52608", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation":